place.name: CUDWORTH
place.gazetteerText: CUDWORTH, a parish in Chard district, Somerset; 3 miles SSE of Ilminster r. station, and 3½ ENE of Chard. Post town, Crick-Malherbie, under Chard. Acres, 1, 077. Real property, £1, 486. Pop., 151. Houses, 29. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Bath and Wells. Value, £50. Patron, the Bishop of Bath and Wells. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
